A team developing a graphical flowchart engine for defining and executing Apache Camel routes seeks an experienced Java developer with extended Apache Camel knowledge. The requirements are as follows:


- Apache Camel.


- Having good experience with relational databases is required. 


- Experience with docker/kubernetes, including invoking them from Camel will be much apreciated.


- Knowing BPMN (activiti/flowable/camunda/jbpm) and SIP aren't required but would be helpful. 


- We don't use Spring/Boot, your knowledge of it would only be helpful as a source of useful patterns.


In Camel, it would be good if you were familiar with components like Jetty, Netty, websockets, SIP, LDAP, Docker etc.


It will be easier if you speak English natively with American accent as it is easier for me to understand, or Russian which is my own native language.


You should study our codebase and be ready to fix errors and add features that will come out from usage of our product, plus assist in writing the documentation. 


Examples of what you may asked to do:


- Integrate Camel Security - the Trust Managers, SSL etc for seamless use in different other components like Http, Ldap etc;


- Create a visual interface for the Camel Tooling, or at least the backend part of it;


- Review our own SIP component and integrate it with security;


- Consult on switching to Camel 3;


Also we expect you to do some common developer tasks like


- Integrate the reporting tools;


- Assemble the convenient distribution; 


- Dockerize the program;


- Integrate automated Unit testing;


- Smoke testing and creating some simple routes/processes with the system;


- Assisting the first users of the program, the technical writers and become a part of the last line of support;


- Limited refactoring to eliminate unneeded API traces of previous refactorings;


- Performance tuning which involves the database pool waits, database indices.


This is our project by the way: http://sborex.com/poc/


To be contacted please show that you've read the requirements, have enough experience and understand whan needs to be done. Please provide some thoughts on how you used to solve similar problems previously.

<b>Hourly Range</b>: $30.00-$70.00


